modules.description: Provides functions for constructing and manipulating buffers to serialize data with minimal copying, supporting direct output to file descriptors or custom writers. Operates on byte sequences and buffer structures, enabling efficient data encoding. Used to implement protocol-specific serializers, such as a JSON encoder that leverages vectorized writes for high-performance network transmission.

Handles asynchronous serialization of Faraday buffers, supporting custom yield and writev operations for network I/O. Operates on Faraday.t and bigstring iovec structures to manage data transmission. Used to efficiently send HTTP payloads over Lwt-based Unix sockets.
